TITLE: 2001 chevy malibu
ATTR: condition: good#cylinders: 6 cylinders#drive: fwd#fuel: gas#odometer: 195000#paint color: brown#size: compact#title status: clean#transmission: automatic#type: sedan
MESSAGE: 2001  chevy malibu#195;000 miles#3.1l v6#automatic#car leaked coolant badly about 10;000 miles ago and i thought the head gasket had gone. turns out it was only the upper intake gaskets leaking. i had it apart and i had the gasket kit anyways so fuck it; i tore the heads off anyways (no head gasket leaks; oh well). so i seated the valves; and replaced the head gaskets as well.#vehicle had a loss of power going up hill(clogged cat); so i pulled the catalytic converter off and banged it out (fixed the problem).#car has a check engine light; probably due to the fact that i turned the catalytic converter into a straight pipe or that i removed the egr system while unecessarily replacing the head gaskets.#while i was at it i replaced the crank shaft sensor; idler pulleys; spark plugs and wires.#about 30;000 miles ago i replaced the fuel pump and fuel filter.#car has minor damage on front driver fender from some old lady backing into me at the gas station.#minor damage on the hood from a tagro truck running something over in front of me on the freeway.#car runs strong; pretty fast for an automatic.#a/c works; windows work; stock stereo (not bad; no blown speakers); trunk leaks a bit; front passenger window switch doesnt work very well.#have to put a half quart of oil in it every month or so.#car doesnt overheat; stays cool inside and out; runs nicely although a bit loudly due to no catalytic converter; but would be a nice cheap ride for somebody. just increased our children amount to 3 and had to buy a bigger vehicle and dont have room for this in my driveway anymore. check engine light isnt a problem if you register it in a county that doesnt require emissions(thats what i did); pretty easy to do. or i suppose you could pass emissions and slow the car down by hooking the egr back up and buying a catalytic converter...#still have the ugly hub caps if you want them.#$1000/obo#show contact info
